# ============================================================================
#   EXCEPTIONS - KEEP THESE FILES
# ============================================================================

# Keep example environment files (remove sensitive data first!)
!.env.example
!.env.template

# Keep specific documentation
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md

# Keep configuration examples
!config/example.json

# ============================================================================
# 📝 NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# Heavy files to avoid:
# - recommendation_service/text_embeddings/ (VERY LARGE)
# - recommendation_service/venv/ (Python virtual environment)
# - node_modules/ (JavaScript dependencies)
# - *.log files (training logs can be huge)
# - ML model files (*.pkl, *.h5, *.model, etc.)
#
# Before pushing:
# 1. Run: git status
# 2. Check file sizes: git ls-files | xargs ls -lh
# 3. If any file > 100MB, add to .gitignore
# 4. Clean history if needed: git filter-branch (careful!)
#
# To check what will be committed:
# git add -n .
#
# To see ignored files:
# git status --ignored
#
# ============================================================================
